SIMPLE: adobe
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adobe
<hw>A*do"be</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*d⟦omac⟧"b⟦asl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Sp.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An unburnt brick dried in the sun;
also used as an adjective, <as>as, an <ex>adobe</ex> house, in Texas or
New Mexico</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Earth from which unburnt bricks are made.</def>
<mark>[Western U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Alluvial and playa clays of
desert and arid regions, differing from ordinary clays of humid regions
in containing carbonates and other soluble minerals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>adobe-lily</ent>⟦br⟧
